<br>
Arg, when she left that butthead my nephew was a living nightmare.  Always crying about never getting his way, always wanting things he couldn't have; things which the idiot (you starting to get my feelings towards that buttwhipe?) would give to the baby just to make him stop crying.  Whenever my sister would finally start getting him to behave, &quot;Dad&quot; would come over for his monthly visit and in the course of only 3 hours, return my nephew's habits back to the old way of the brat.<br>
<br>
Spanking is a very good way of teaching kids right-and-wrong.  Psychologically is creates a relationship trigger within the pschye of the child that &quot;If I do that, then I will be spanked and get hurt.&quot;  So during early ages when liguistics are not exactly their best, physical discipline is most effective.  Which will a 2-year-old understand; &quot;Don't do that, you'll poke your eye out and go blind.&quot; or pain on the backside.<br>
<br>
As a child gets older, then you can ween off the physical punishment for your mental and psychological punishment.  My mother always liked to use &quot;The Silent Treatment&quot;.<br>
<br>
But seriously; in my book a spanking is taking a kid over your knee, pulling down their pants, and just bare palm to ass for 5 or 6 times.  Any further than that and it becomes what I would consider a beating; and that's taking it way to far. <p><table width="*%">
